    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1892-12-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1892-12-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="191"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d191">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">White</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Foster</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1892-12-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 10, 1892</hi>
                        </date>. (Received December 21.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 865.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to your instruction No. 951 of the 5th
                    ultimo, and to my dispatch No. 841 of November 21, I have the honor to acquaint
                    you that Lord Rosebery informed me during a recent interview which I had with
                    his lordship in reference to other matters, that orders have been circulated by
                    the admiralty to commanders of Her Majesty’s ships, directing them to recognize
                    in the usual manner the United States consular agent in the Gilbert Islands.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Henry White.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
